Reviews.Title: Great Cable and A Great Price
Reviews.Author: Donald L. Moore Jr. "DubbaDon"
Reviews.Content: I needed an extension for a whole home FM transmitter (Brand: Fail Safe, also available at Amazon), so that I could get better ranch with the transmitter (without being illegal). This cable let me extend the transmitting antenna to a decent location. The molded connectors are well built and have stood up well.

Reviews.Title: It's a cable. It worked
Reviews.Author: Andy
Reviews.Content: Since it had the right connectors on each end and was the right length, I'm going to go ahead and say that it met my expectations. Thank YOU 25 ft black BNC cable.

Reviews.Title: Works well with HD Video Switcher
Reviews.Author: RhinoATL
Reviews.Content: I bought these to use with our new BlackMagic Design HD video setup and these work great! Quality is good and the somewhat finicky ATEM 2 M/E seems to like them. I've heard that when you are using HD video it's best to try and stay in the 75 ohm cable range. Not quite sure if that's "textbook" or not, but they seem to work just fine.

Reviews.Title: It's a wire
Reviews.Author: Rick
Reviews.Content: You have a copper wire with two capped ends. It works and I could not see much degradation of quality from 5 feet to 25 feet.
